Jpn long - term rates too low - ex - MOF official quoted . Makoto Utsumi , a former Japanese vice finance minister for international affairs , said that current long - term interest rates are too low and reflect excessive pessimism about the outlook for the Japanese economy , a foreign wire service reported on Wednesday . The report quoted Utsumi , who is now a professor at Keio University , as saying in an interview that current Japanese long - term interest rates of below three percent reflect a " too pessimistic " view of the Japanese economy as they assume economic growth of below two percent . Utsumi was also quoted as saying the Bank of Japan will have a difficult time raising interest rates until a recovery in the economy can be confirmed . He declined to elaborate further , the report said . - - Tokyo Treasury Desk + 81 - 3 - 5473 - 3748 
